herin and associated protein catenins functions role of cell adhesion in establishing docking machinery for transport vesicles iii in vitro studies of protein organization and interactions in purified and reconstituted cell systems iv in vivo studies of embryonic development of polarized renal epithelia in the normal mouse and the cpk mouse mutant a murine strain with autosomal recessive polycystic kidney disease in which cell polarity is partially reversed publications plasma selenium level before diagnosis and the risk of prostate cancer development brooks jd metter ej chan dw sokoll lj landis p nelson wg muller d andres r carter hb j urol 2001 166 6 2034 8 listeria monocytogenes exploits normal host cell processes to spread from cell to cell robbins jr barth ai marquis h de hostos el nelson wj theriot ja j cell biol 1999 146 6 1333 50 dynamics of b catenin interactions with apc protein regulate epithelial tubulogenesis nelson wj pollack al barth aim altschuler y and mostov ke j cell biol 1997 nh2 terminal deletion of b catenin results in stable co localization of mutant b catenin with apc protein and altered mdck cell adhesion nelson wj barth aim pollack al altschuler y mostov ke j cell biol 1997 origins of cell polarity drubin dg nelson wj cell 1996 84 3 335 44 view all 8 you are here home faculty navigation for this section department of biology education & training courses faculty research sites about us contact us search profiles by name help community academic profiles stanford only login update your profile connect with colleagues find a researcher profiles by name profiles by department profiles by program help go stanford only login update your profile connect with colleagues site navigation home faculty education & training biology events giving to biology stanford medicine resources stanford medicine getting care overview find a physician find a clinical care center stanford hospital & clinics lucile packard children's hospital emergency research overvi